President Obama announced his intent to nominate Mark C. Storella as Ambassador to the Republic of Zambia and Matthew J. Bryza as Ambassador to the Republic of Azerbaijan. Storella is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as the Senior Coordinator for Iraqi Refugees and Internally Displaced Persons at the U.S. Embassy in Baghdad. Bryza is also a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and most recently served as the Deputy Assistant Secretary of European and Eurasian Affairs. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Melissa Savage and C. Kenneth Smith as members on the Board of Directors of the Valles Caldera Trust. Savage is the director of the Four Corners Institute and specializes in fire ecology and southwestern conifer ecosystems. Smith is an associate professor of Forestry and Geology at the University of the South and has experience in regional water issues.